Our Impact

Accounts of our Accomplishments and Meaningful Impact

The World Health Organization has reported that an estimated of 32% of World Wide deaths occur due to cardiovascular diseases with one of the major reasons being the unavailability of medical equipment at primary healthcare centres and clinics. Spandan, a portable ECG device, was curated to tackle this problem. Recording around 10 Lakh heartbeats and employed by 500+ doctors, Spandan has opened new doorways towards preventive healthcare.

Tales of Triumph

The Kedarnath Story

In a daring response to the heart health crisis faced by pilgrims during the Kedarnath Yatra, Sunfox Technologies, and the Uttarakhand Government set out to make a substantial impact. The rising fatalities due to cardiac events in the treacherous terrains of Kedarnath posed a formidable challenge that demanded an innovative solution.
Learn More

The Rajkot Chapter (2023)

In a heartening display of innovation meeting urgent healthcare needs, Spandan ECG’s crucial role at Sarapdad Primary Health Centre (PHC) in Rajkot district stands as a beacon of hope and a testament to the power of technology in saving lives.

Spandan x LLR Meerut Medical College

Featured in “Medical Reports and Case Studies 2023” , this case study highlights the significant impact of the Spandan ECG device in managing a complex cardiac condition at Lala Lajpat Rai Memorial (LLRM) Medical College, Meerut.

In a groundbreaking initiative, Sunfox Technologies joined forces with EMCURE Pharmaceuticals to significantly enhance cardiac care in remote regions of India. This partnership aimed to transform healthcare delivery in areas where medical facilities were previously limited.

OUR SOLUTIONS

Heart Attack Management
System

The heart attack management system is a specialised setup that provides fast and effective care for people experiencing heart attacks. It has a skilled medical team and advanced equipment to quickly diagnose and treat heart attacks, aiming to minimise damage to the heart and improve outcomes.

Learn More

OUR SOLUTIONS

Ischemia Prevention
Village Programme

Under IPVP, a specialised setup will help to provide fast and effective care for people experiencing heart attacks. The residents will be trained in order to provide early prevention and save lives.
